	     Two men died on the N1 at the Koeberg interchange in Cape Town, after a truck overturned and landed on the roof of the vehicle they were travelling in.WATCH Beaufort West - A man was killed in a fatal accident on the N1 on Saturday morning. Western Cape Traffic Chief, Kenny Africa, said the accident had occurred at around 04:15 on the N1, heading to Beaufort West, roughly 62km from Laingsburg. He said it appeared that the driver of a Ford Figo had lost control of the vehicle and the car had overturned, resulting in the death of a 20-year-old male passenger. Africa said in a separate incident, two drivers were arrested for being under the influence of alcohol on the N1 outside Laingsburg at around 07:00 on Saturday morning. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  